# file_contexts — assigns SELinux labels to files on the filesystem.
#
# FORMAT:
#   <path_regex>    <label>
#
# This file is processed by the build system and merged into the device's
# combined file_contexts. At boot, the init process labels all files
# matching these patterns with the specified SELinux type.
#
# WHY THIS FILE IS NEEDED:
#   Without an entry here, /vendor/bin/potvolumed gets the generic
#   vendor_file label. The init_daemon_domain() macro in potvolumed.te
#   requires the binary to have the potvolumed_exec type for the domain
#   transition to work. If the binary has the wrong label, init runs it
#   in the wrong domain (or init_daemon_domain simply doesn't trigger).
#
# VERIFY ON DEVICE:
#   adb shell ls -laZ /vendor/bin/potvolumed
#   Expected: u:object_r:potvolumed_exec:s0

/vendor/bin/potvolumed    u:object_r:potvolumed_exec:s0
